I wonder if Coker, or whoever has the rights to the XZX molds would be able to
make an XZX with a reinforced or D loader carcass?  They make the 185R14 XZX
in regular non reinforced (common size for many classic sports cars) and I bet
Cooper or whoever's insides they use might make an appropriate core.  Could be
an interesting niche for one of the big list vendors if they could get a run
of several 100 made, would be correct across the board for restorations for a
good 15 years of bus/vanagon production.
 
